The words of description above are insults thrown at me by my friends and even some of my family members. They say things like, &ldquo;Why did you buy such an expensive laptop? It&rsquo;s just for coding anyway.&rdquo;
My initial reaction was anger, and I now tend to avoid people who say such things. To others, a laptop may only be a device that supports the needs of office workers, students, or heavy gamers.
